  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nThe Kademlia p2p pong is supposed to be the hash of the ping, according to page 4 of [this (PDF) paper](http://www.cs.bu.edu/~goldbe/projects/eclipseEth.pdf), which has a nice summary of the p2p protocol. The paper claims that without this check, \"*pong* messages [could be] sent from spoofed IP addresses\".\r\n\r\nHere's where I expected a check:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/eb7138ae67caab09c16d886f59e54639ad97b522/p2p/kademlia.py#L425-L433\r\n\r\nIs this implemented somewhere else, or some reason that we don't need the check?\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nCheck the pong result against the hash of the ping, failing the pong if it is mismatched.\r\n",
