    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I had to refresh my memory because it's been a while since this code was written, but it turns out we are already performing that check when we receive a pong. This is how it works:\r\n1. When we [send a ping, we get the msg hash](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/p2p/discovery.py#L190-L191) and [generate a pingid, combining the hash with the node's ID](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/p2p/kademlia.py#L470)\r\n2. That pingid is then used to track [pongs we are waiting for](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/p2p/kademlia.py#L484)\r\n3. [If we get a pong with a hash different than what we expect, we drop it](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/p2p/kademlia.py#L342-L349)",
